OL,4,CGive people the right to switch off
OL,5,Cafter work - Labour
OL,6, Workers should be given the "right to
OL,7, switch off" when they have left for the
OL,8, day to ensure homes don't become "24/7
OL,9, offices", Labour has said.
OL,11,FThe party also wants employees to have
OL,12,Fthe right to flexible practices such as
OL,13,Fworking from home.
OL,15,FThis would allow people to spend more
OL,16,Ftime with their families instead of
OL,17,Fcommuting, says Labour.
OL,19,FThe government says it has no plans to
OL,20,Fintroduce a legal right to work from
OL,21,Fhome.
